When the stars come out and the sun goes down, do you think about the fact that you won't be hydrating for roughly 8 hours?

That's why dehydration relief throughout the day is key. Not only does staying properly hydrated make falling asleep easier by regulating your core body temp, it also makes you more likely to wake up in a good mood the next day (studies show that people who go to bed hydrated wake up feeling more positive emotions).

Asking for a friend....🙋‍♀️ We want to leave you with a couple quick tips to wrap up #StressAwarenessMonth.👇

Remember, your brain and body work as a team 🧠 When your body is under physical stress (i.e. going about your day-to-day tasks while dehydrated) it can increase your stress levels and negatively impact your mood.

The next time you find yourself turning to a search engine for answers 🔎, check in with yourself first to ensure your basic needs are being met.

Ask yourself...
Am I well-hydrated?
Am I giving my body enough nutrients?
Am I getting adequate sleep?

If the answer is no, you know where to start. We recommend DripDrop for #dehydrationrelieffast and one less stress 😌

Read more on our new blog post: 10 Ways to Manage Stress. Link in bio.

Even if meditation isn’t your thing 🧘, there are other ways to relieve stress during #NationalStressAwarenessMonth. 👇

Our #1 tip for keeping stress at bay is to stay hydrated. You may be thinking..."it's not that simple." Hear us out. All of our organs, including our brains, need hydration to function properly. When you're dehydrated, your body isn't running well - leading to increased cortisol, AKA the stress hormone, and (you guessed it) higher levels of stress 😣

TLDR: When you're feeling overwhelmed, try drinking DripDrop 💦 Managing your stress may be as simple as giving your body what it needs. #dehydrationrelieffast
